cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new approach to modeling derived predicates in domain-independent planning models using axioms, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of axioms in planning models, which is related to logical reasoning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes new planners based on answer set programming and integer programming. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the search space and plan length of planning models, which are related to algorithmic efficiency. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new approach to planning models, which is relevant to software engineering.
